(3829,	2,	'2012-09-15T17:00:00+0100-432081580177851@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'CropShare Harvest Party',	'Come to CropShare\'s annual harvest celebration down on the farm! <br/> <br/>Bring a bottle and something to put on the BBQ, other food and drink provided <br/> <br/>Live band- Allotment <br/> <br/>Bonfire  <br/> <br/>Plenty of activities- <br/> <br/>Felt making <br/>Wool spinning <br/>Grind your own rye flour from our home grown grain <br/>Kids straw fun  <br/> <br/>Spaces for camping overnight available - get in touch via cambridge(at)cropshare.org.uk to book. <br/> <br/>£5 suggested dontation <br/> <br/>See you there!',	'2012-09-15 18:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/432081580177851/',	'Willow Farm, Lode, CB25 9HF',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3830,	2,	'2012-10-18T19:30:00+0100-233595016768932@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - The Turning Point',	'Come and see this great documentary about how a community in Scotland is making the transition to a more resilient and sustainable way of life. The film takes as its starting point an international conference on \'Positive Energy: Creative Community Responses to Peak Oil and Climate Change\', which took place at the Findhorn Ecovillage Community in Scotlandin March 2008. It explores positive and practical solutions, with examples from the Findhorn community and Transition Town Forres that demonstratehow we can tackle food and energy production, transport, and wastewatertreatment. It also shows how a local currency can help to boost the localeconomy. \'This film is a great introduction to peak oil, resilience, and rediscovering community. It is a practical exploration of how to build resilience in a peak oil world, offering a glimpse of the possibilities ofan economic, social and cultural renaissance that is just over the horizon.\' says Maddy Harland, editor of Permaculture magazine. The film will be followed by a short discussion (probably moving to the Six Bells Pub when the cafe closes at 9pm). Free, all welcome.',	'2012-10-18 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/233595016768932/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3831,	2,	'2012-11-01T19:30:00+0000-166582920148088@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - Recycled crafts',	'This cafe evening will focus on crafts using recycled materials. One thing we\'ll be making is \'plabric\' - converting plastic bags into astronger material which can be used to make other items. And if you can bring along a few non-degradable and attractively coloured plastic bags to work with, that\'d be great!',	'2012-11-01 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/166582920148088/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3832,	2,	'2012-11-15T19:30:00+0000-513312278693506@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - Woodland management',	'Vince and Louise, volunteer wardens at Hardwick Wood owned bythe Wildlife Trust will come and tell us about their experience. They manage the wood to encourage wildlife and also produce a large amount of sustainable wood products. The aim is to replicate the traditional coppice management in parts of the wood, which makes it better for wildflowers, lots of insects, and a greater variety of birds and bats etc. They produce firewood, some charcoal, garden sticks and structures etc. and deliver tocustomers around the area to raise funds for the Wildlife Trust. There has also been some much larger tree-felling work by professionals to supply timber for buildings etc. <br/> <br/>Vince and Liz will also invite you to join them on one of their work days to get some practical experience. After the talk the next work days are 17th November and 1st December.',	'2012-11-15 20:30:00',	'2012-11-15 22:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/513312278693506/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3833,	2,	'2012-12-13T19:30:00+0000-360646267364507@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cambridge Christmas Party',	'Live music, mince pies and more - we hope you can come along to TC\'s Christmas party! All welcome, free, bring cakes if you like, buy drinks from the cafe, and enjoy a well-deserved rest after all the Transition activities recently!',	'2012-12-13 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/360646267364507/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3834,	2,	'2013-01-10T19:30:00+0000-190416364431902@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - How to save energy at home',	'There are many ways you can reduce your energy use at home without spending a penny - just by the things you do. From closing curtains at night or turning the heating off half an hour before you go to bed, to not overfilling the kettle, turning off the TV when no-one is watching it... This workshop is about what we can do, why we don\'t always do it andwhat we can do to make it easier. <br/>Nicola Terry gave this workshop first at Warm Homes in Trumpington and got good reviews. It will be even better this time.',	'2013-01-10 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/190416364431902/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3835,	2,	'2013-01-13T17:30:00+0000-429731303766927@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Media group - Transition Free Press (and startup discussion)',	'I\'m going to start something, which will either be a new Transition group, or me sitting in a cafe on my own moodily supping soya lattes until I get thrown out. The idea is to have a \'media\' group which looksat general awareness of Transition events and activities, how they affect Cambridge, and what we positive moves we could make to improve things. <br/> <br/>For me personally, this will be largely about learning, by going through press stories and group discussions. But we\'ll also try and have a context to do some voluntary journalism or design work to support the other groups. <br/> <br/>For this first session I will bring along several preview copiesof the Transition Free Press, a newspaper for the movement which you\'re welcome to browse through and discuss, and we\'ll also have a discussion about helpful blogs and twitters to follow.',	'2013-01-13 18:30:00',	'2013-01-13 21:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/429731303766927/',	'',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3836,	2,	'2013-01-27T17:30:00+0000-105463922957528@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Media group - What does Transition need to communicate?',	'There are a couple of talks in recent times about science communication, Rosie\'s talk for CCF yesterday and the Transition Cafe with Jade in two weeks. Unfortunately I\'ve had other plans prevent me from going to either of them but am very interested to hear a summary, they sound brill! <br/> <br/>I thought it would be good to focus the media group on the question of what Transition (and Transition Cambridge) need to communicate, whether it\'s through science or otherwise. What do we need to make people aware of, in order to get more people involved, change public attitudes, and shape a more pleasant future? I propose a discussion for around an hour and a half, with some readings from books/blogs on the subject, and thensome more discursory plotting if anyone wants to stay on. <br/> <br/>I\'ll be upstairs in CB1, with some Transition literature on the table to make myself easier to find!',	'2013-01-27 18:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/105463922957528/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3837,	2,	'2013-03-03T17:30:00+0000-425486960872612@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Media Group - Transition Free Press first edition',	'Hi, I\'d like to hold a session to take a look at the first edition of the Transition Free Press and discuss the stories inside. If anyone wants to publicise a Transition event and particularly if they want to try reaching a broader audience, free free to bring it along for a brainstorm.',	'2013-03-03 18:30:00',	'2013-03-03 20:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/425486960872612/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3838,	2,	'2013-03-07T19:30:00+0000-362021983912814@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - \'How secure is your financial future?\'',	'Does it any longer make sense to save for your retirement in the current economic climate? If so, what kinds of sustainable savings or investments will offer you the best returns? Come along to discuss these issues in the context of peak oil and the global financial climate, and share ways to take a positive look at managing your money. We\'ll also look at setting up further events to explore the practical options in more detail with a view to enabling us all to make informed decisions.',	'2013-03-07 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/362021983912814/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3839,	2,	'2013-06-24T18:45:00+0100-202612339863071@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Food Grower\'s Circle',	'Have questions and queries about your food growing endeavours?Then come along to our Food Grower\'s Circle. <br/>A knowledge sharing group for food growers of all experiences. Just bring along your food growing questions and collectively we\'ll provide answers and solutions. <br/> <br/>These meetings are free, friendly and informal.  Just fellow food growers with cuppas in hand. <br/> <br/>6.45pm for a 7pm start. <br/> <br/>Future dates: <br/>Monday 8th July at CB2 cafe, Norfolk Street. <br/>Monday 22nd July  (location tbc) <br/>Monday 12th August (location tbc) <br/>Monday 26th August (location tbc)',	'2013-06-24 19:45:00',	'2013-06-24 21:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/202612339863071/',	'CB2',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-0/p180x540/966617_10151595473184765_1425640956_o.jpg'),
(3840,	2,	'2013-07-02T18:30:00+0100-142535732616365@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Fruit Harvest Project - 1st exploratory meeting',	'Transition Cambridge food group is launching an Abundance Project - aiming to make use of unwanted or excess fruit from city gardens. Ifyou have energy to get involved, please come to our meeting with any of the following: ideas, inspiration, experience and offers of assistance and /or equipment! More info here <a href=\'http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTFood.FruitHarvestProject\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTFood.FruitHarvestProject</a> ',	'2013-07-02 19:30:00',	'2013-07-02 21:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/142535732616365/',	'CB2',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3841,	2,	'2013-07-08T18:45:00+0100-295571440578644@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Food Grower\'s Circle',	'Have questions and queries about your food growing endeavours?Then come along to our Food Grower\'s Circle. <br/>A knowledge sharing group for food growers of all experiences. Just bring along your food growing questions and collectively we\'ll provide answers and solutions. <br/> <br/>These meetings are free, friendly and informal.  Just fellow food growers with cuppas in hand. <br/> <br/>6.45pm for a 7pm start. <br/> <br/>Future dates: <br/>Monday 22nd July(location tbc) <br/>Monday 12th August (location tbc) <br/>Monday 26th August (location tbc)',	'2013-07-08 19:45:00',	'2013-07-08 21:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/295571440578644/',	'CB2',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-0/p180x540/979938_10151601982514765_606886049_o.jpg'),
(3842,	2,	'2013-07-20T11:00:00+0100-513381502048779@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Want to spend more time in Nature? Join our Wildlife Wanderings. <br/>   <br/> A leisurely meander through Coldhams\'s Common, taking our time to observe the nature that is taking place around us.  <br/>  <br/> Meet at the gates to Coldham\'s Common, on Coldham\'s Lane, opposite Cromwell Road - <a href=\'http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&tab=wl\' target=\'_blank\'>http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&tab=wl</a>  <br/>   <br/> Bring a little notebook and pencil if you fancy starting a nature journal, we can show you how. <br/>   <br/> Please bring hats, suncream, suitable shoes and water. <br/>   <br/> And bring some simple healthy food to share, if you fancy staying for a picnic after. <br/>   <br/> Free and open to everyone.',	'2013-07-20 12:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/513381502048779/',	'Coldham\'s Common',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1014786_10151624665864765_814720712_o.jpg'),
(3843,	2,	'2013-07-22T19:30:00+0100-156029301253163@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Food Grower\'s Circle',	'Upstairs in CB2.  Look out for a table full of veg growing books. <br/> <br/>We\'ll be discussing whats going on in our garden right now and how we overcome some of the challenges.  <br/> <br/>Join us for an informal and friendly chat, over something cool and refreshing.',	'2013-07-22 20:30:00',	'2013-07-22 21:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/156029301253163/',	'CB2',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-0/p180x540/1077665_10151683353694765_891629026_o.jpg'),
(3844,	2,	'2013-07-25T19:30:00+0100-1400418343506178@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Transition Cafe - Growing Spaces',	'Come to the cafe this week for some inspiration! Stephanie hasbeen leading this Transition Cambridge project based on edible landscaping, and this is an opportunity to hear all about it and see some inspiringtransformations of public spaces. Previously neglected public spaces are now growing luscious harvests of fruit, herbs and veg right here in Cambridge.',	'2013-07-25 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1400418343506178/',	'CB1',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3845,	2,	'2013-08-20T18:30:00+0100-1405297519693835@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Fruit Harvest Project meeting',	'2nd meeting of Transition Cambridge\'s newest sub group. There\'ll be various event opportunities to discuss and plan for, plus updates on city fruit surplusses and a number of apple events... all welcome!',	'2013-08-20 19:30:00',	'2013-08-20 21:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1405297519693835/',	'',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3846,	2,	'2013-08-31T11:00:00+0100-518691918179836@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Want to spend more time in Nature?  Then join our Wildlife Wanderings.  <br/>   <br/> We\'ll be exploring Paradise Fen, at a slow and inquisitive pace, looking out for different plants, insects and signs of animals. <br/>   <br/> Meeting point: The ice-cream shop, next to the paddling pool at Lammas Land. <a href=\'http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&tab=wl\' target=\'_blank\'>http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&tab=wl</a>  <br/>   <br/> Remember to bring a little notebook and pencil if you\'d like to keep a Nature journal.  We can show you how.  <br/>  <br/> Also bring hat, suncream, suitable shoes and water. <br/>   <br/> And if you\'d like to stay for a picnic afterwards, then bring some simple healthy food to share. <br/>  <br/>Free and open to everyone.',	'2013-08-31 12:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/518691918179836/',	'Paradise Fen Nature Reserve, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1052454_10151624675524765_195709739_o.jpg'),
(3847,	2,	'2013-09-24T18:30:00+0100-158073271066174@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Fruit Harvest Project  Meeting',	'we want to  locate and redistribute  unwanted fruit from Cambridge gardens, we have some plans and a few hands, come and join us at our more or less monthly meet up! We\'re upstairs at the back table usually.',	'2013-09-24 19:30:00',	'2013-09-24 21:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/158073271066174/',	'CB2 Bistro',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3848,	2,	'2013-10-26T14:00:00+0100-639200159434939@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Logan\'s Meadow LNR',	'An informal wander around one of Cambridge\'s eight Local Nature Reserves.  Collectively we closely observe the plants, insects, birds and other wildlife we can find.  All welcome.  Please bring sensible shoesthat you dont mind getting muddy, a waterproof coat and some water.   <br/>Please note the image above is not from Logan\'s Meadow.',	'2013-10-26 15:00:00',	'2013-10-26 16:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/639200159434939/',	'Logan\'s Meadow, Logan\'s Way, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1294528_10151868508034765_101979587_o.jpg'),
(3849,	2,	'2013-11-23T11:00:00+0000-465279253592687@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'A informal and leisurely wander round one of our little known nature reserves.  Please bring stout shoes, warm clothes, water and a notebook if you fancy recording the nature we observe.  <br/> <br/>Please meet at entrance off Nutting Road. <br/>Walk will be about 1 hour long. <br/> <br/>All welcome!!',	'2013-11-23 12:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/465279253592687/',	'Barnwell East LNR, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1425378_10151957687424765_1045646213_o.jpg'),
(3850,	2,	'2013-12-07T11:00:00+0000-737531802942809@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us for an informal, un-guided wander round Clare Wood, Cambridge. <br/> <br/>We meet once a month to take a leisurely stroll through Cambridge\'s green places, stopping to observe little aspects of nature, as we go.  <br/> <br/>The wanders last for 1-1.5 hours.  <br/> <br/>Meet at the Trumpington Road - Brooklands Avenue traffic lights, on the Botanic gardens corner. <br/> <br/>Please bring stout shoes, warm clothes and water. <br/> <br/>All welcome, including families. <br/> <br/>Any questions just leave a message on the event page.  <br/> <br/>We\'ll be heading over to Mill Road Winter Fair, just after.',	'2013-12-07 12:00:00',	'2013-12-07 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/737531802942809/',	'Brooklands Avenue, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/q83/s720x720/904168_10151977172904765_879515980_o.jpg'),
(3851,	2,	'2014-01-04T11:00:00+0000-580060112070808@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us for a wintery walk around Logan\'s Meadow.  <br/>Meet at the bottom of Logan\'s Way, at the entrance of the nature reserve. <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is an informal and friendly gathering of folk, who take a steady stroll around green spaces to admire the beauty and ingenuity of nature. <br/> <br/>Please bring stout shoes, warm layers and some water.  The site is likely to be muddy. <br/> <br/>All welcome: including families. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://lnr.cambridge.gov.uk/reserves/logans_meadow/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://lnr.cambridge.gov.uk/reserves/logans_meadow/</a> ',	'2014-01-04 12:00:00',	'2014-01-04 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/580060112070808/',	'Logan\'s Meadow, Logan\'s Way, Chesterton, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1484048_10152051504839765_76897389_o.jpg'),
(3852,	2,	'2014-01-30T19:30:00+0000-602355109801000@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Permies in pubs',	'An informal event for people into Permaculture, for support and encouragement to meet monthly. To get you thinking about it again. Hopesome of you can come.',	'2014-01-30 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/602355109801000/',	'The Six Bells pub, 11 Covent Garden, CB1 2HS',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-0/p180x540/1547992_1474036979489893_1430766337_o.jpg'),
(3853,	2,	'2014-02-15T11:00:00+0000-653822394659773@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us for a ramble round Coldham\'s Common. <br/>Looking out for signs of bees, frogs, ladybirds and lesser celandine. <br/> <br/>Bring wet weather gear, stout shoes and a drink of water, as walking can be thirsty business. <br/> <br/>All welcome.',	'2014-02-15 12:00:00',	'2014-02-15 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/653822394659773/',	'Coldham\'s Common, entrance opposite Cromwell Road',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1606263_10152110609479765_2106745313_o.jpg'),
(3854,	2,	'2014-02-27T19:30:00+0000-286277774855123@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Permaculture in Pubs',	'For encouragement and support and for anyone who wants to knowmore about this subject. Everyone\'s welcome',	'2014-02-27 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/286277774855123/',	'Six Bells',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3855,	2,	'2014-03-29T11:00:00+0000-403704376441907@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'With signs of spring join us for an exploration of Bramblefields LNR in Chesterton. <a href=\'http://lnr.cambridge.gov.uk/reserves/bramblefields/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://lnr.cambridge.gov.uk/reserves/bramblefields/</a>  <br/> <br/>We\'ll be in search of frogs and newts breeding in the pond and hawthornand blackthorn blossoms. <br/> <br/>Please bring waterproof clothing, stout shoes and some water to drink. <br/> <br/>All welcome.',	'2014-03-29 12:00:00',	'2014-03-29 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/403704376441907/',	'Bramblefields LNR, Laxton Way entrance.',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1511606_10152110642899765_690361127_o.jpg'),
(3856,	2,	'2014-04-26T10:45:00+0100-435312236613729@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us to explore the wet meadows of Stourbridge Common and admire the wildlife of the river Cam. Wildlife Wanderings is a friendly andinformal gathering of local people who want to get to know their local green spaces a little bit better. We will meet at 10.45am at the Riverside entrance of the common (CB5 8HN) for a 11am start. Please bring walking shoes, a waterproof jacket and plenty of water. All welcome, including families.',	'2014-04-26 11:45:00',	'2014-04-26 13:15:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/435312236613729/',	'Stourbridge Common',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1932720_10152261592764765_1836075065_o.jpg'),
(3857,	2,	'2014-05-30T19:30:00+0100-643549552394492@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Meet the Buzz Tour',	'<a href=\'http://buzztour.org\' target=\'_blank\'>http://buzztour.org</a>  <br/> <br/>The Buzz Tour is a walking tour the length and breadth of England visiting people protecting the environment. <br/> <br/>There are flowers of change blooming all over England, for a future without fossil fuels! We can help pollinate those beautiful blooms and spread the seeds of change. Weâ€™re visiting inspiring people and projects the length of England. From permaculture farms to divestment campaigns, WI groups to direct action. We want culture change not climate change. <br/> <br/>Eve and her entourage are visiting Cambridge for three days, and would like to meetTransitioners and others who are involved in creating a positive future. We have the upstairs room at the Emperor pub booked for the evening.',	'2014-05-30 20:30:00',	'2014-05-31 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/643549552394492/',	'The Emperor Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/q84/s720x720/10417506_10152397371780033_3593952739228860990_n.jpg?oh=c93a715a644f74a77f2cf0416527fcc7&oe=5882D8B1'),
(3858,	2,	'2014-05-31T10:45:00+0100-246394738893654@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us for another wildlife wanderings, but this time out atByron\'s Pool; famous skinny dipping spot for Lord Byron and Rupert Brooke (so I have been told). No skinny dipping planned for the wandering, butlots of wildlife spotting. <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is a friendly informal gathering of Cambridge residents who want to get to know their green spaces better. We will meet at 10.45am for a 11am start, at the entrance to Bryon\'s Pool LNR. <br/> <br/>Please bring sensible shoes, a waterproof and plenty of water.',	'2014-05-31 11:45:00',	'2014-05-31 13:15:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/246394738893654/',	'Byron\'s Pool LNR',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10275552_10152355312764765_1748827786728703134_o.jpg'),
(3859,	2,	'2014-06-21T10:45:00+0100-330364890451419@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings',	'Join us a Fulbourn Fen, for another Wildlife Wanderings, where we hope to see that last of this season\'s orchids on this ancient grassland. <br/> <br/>Wildlife Wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of localpeople who want to get to know their green spaces better.  We take a casual wander around the site looking for different plants and animals. <br/> <br/>Allwelcome, including children.  Meet at entrance on Stourbridge Lane. <br/> <br/>Please bring sensible shoes, and plenty of water. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.wildlifebcn.org/reserves/fulbourn-fen\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.wildlifebcn.org/reserves/fulbourn-fen</a> ',	'2014-06-21 11:45:00',	'2014-06-21 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/330364890451419/',	'Fulbourn Fen Nature Reserve',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10286923_10152406309939765_467250080059551412_o.jpg'),
(3860,	2,	'2014-07-29T19:00:00+0100-657063141055638@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Food Group Annual Summer Outing',	'Join us for our traditional \'end of term\' summer outing -  an evening bike ride to the  community pub in Horningsea for a meal and a fewdrinkies, they serve vegetarian food and eggs from their own free ranging  pub garden chickens.  <br/>The cycle posse will leave from outside the Green Dragon pub, (Water Street, Chesterton CB4 1NZ) at 6.15pm for a leisurely riverside cycle ride (taking the bikes over the bridge at Baits Bite lock.) You can check the route here <a href=\'http://www.cyclestreets.net/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.cyclestreets.net/</a>   <br/>Car travel is also happening for those who don\'t want to cycle. - contact Jacky Sutton-Adam to book your place and also if you want to lift share.',	'2014-07-29 20:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/657063141055638/',	'The Plough and Fleece',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3861,	2,	'2014-07-30T22:15:00+0100-290470794471149@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'For Wildlife Wanderings - Wildlife Trust: Glowworm Survey.',	'Without a Wildlife Wanderings event this month, I thought some of you might enjoy joining me for this. <br/> <br/>Helping the wildlife trust survey glow worms at Cherry Hinton Chalk Pits.  <br/> <br/>See the website below formore details: <br/><a href=\'http://www.wildlifebcn.org/events/2014/07/30/east-pit-glow-worm-survey?instance=0\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.wildlifebcn.org/events/2014/07/30/east-pit-glow-worm-survey?instance=0</a>  <br/> <br/>Photo Credit: Laura Watson',	'2014-07-30 23:15:00',	'2014-07-31 00:55:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/290470794471149/',	'East Pit, Cherry Hinton, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/10577179_10152508625834765_4306508729774845187_n.jpg?oh=0833e35edfd663d923aa97cac05b449b&oe=587F90EC'),
