(3871,	2,	'2014-10-25T14:15:00+0100-353484988151047@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Clare Wood',	'Join us for our first Autumn walk of 2014. <br/>We will be taking a casual wander through Clare Wood, with the aim of looking out for fungiand other signs of Autumn. <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of local people who want to get to know their local green spaces better.  <br/> <br/>All are welcome, including families. <br/> <br/>Please bring along warm clothing, sturdy footwear and a bottle of water.  <br/> <br/>Meeting Point: On Trumpington Road, in front of Brooklands Lodge (type \'Brooklands Lodge, Cambridge\' into Google maps to find location). <br/> <br/>Time: 2.15pm for a2.30pm start.',	'2014-10-25 15:15:00',	'2014-10-25 17:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/353484988151047/',	'Clare Wood, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1888909_10152713544199765_6946923426760462894_o.jpg'),
(3872,	2,	'2014-10-29T18:00:00+0000-288528414687796@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Nature Writing in the City',	'A series of 9 monthly creative writing workshops which aims tolook at the relationship between people and the natural world. Price: £10per session',	'2014-10-29 19:00:00',	'2014-10-29 21:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/288528414687796/',	'The Earl of Beaconsfield',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/s720x720/10629599_10152352488741087_327243798997125839_n.jpg?oh=c15aa976cb8abbc1b515e9ae6c2bf02d&oe=58720D70'),
(3873,	2,	'2014-11-22T14:15:00+0000-1583546351874270@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Bramblefields LNR',	'Join us for a wintery walk around Bramblefields Local Nature Reserve, in anticipation of the arrival of Redwings and Fieldfares. <br/> <br/>TheEuropean autumn draws in a migration of thrushes from Scandinavia and Russia, and Bramblefields LNR has been known as a great feeding site for these birds, who will winter in the UK until the weather warms up further north. <br/> <br/>Not only will we look out for our wintering neighbours, but we will also continue our hunt for fungal species amongst the scrub and the grasslands.  <br/> <br/>Wildlife Wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of local people who want to get to know their green spaces better and appreciate local wildlife.  <br/> <br/>All are welcome, including families.  <br/> <br/>Please bring lots of warm layers and good walking shoes. <br/>Do bring binoculars as well, if you have some.  <br/> <br/>Meeting point: Laxton Way entrance to the Bramblefields site at 2.15pm for a 2.30pm start.',	'2014-11-22 15:15:00',	'2014-11-22 17:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1583546351874270/',	'Bramblefields LNR, Laxton Way, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-0/p180x540/1797546_10152742675284765_3812193861977222646_n.jpg?oh=921293ae63d29d562851193bb1cfa2c4&oe=588339D9'),
(3874,	2,	'2014-11-25T19:30:00+0000-623496104425966@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'LOW ENERGY LIGHTING FORUM',	'Andrew Davis, the founder of My Green Lighting will present the latest in low energy lighting products, both fluorescent and LED that you might actually want to use. <br/>See the latest products in action, and learn about some of the common pit-falls when buying low energy lights for your home. <br/>Low energy lighting probably doesn\'t deserve the bad reputation that it might have - things have come a long way in the last few years. Come and see the light for yourself. A discount of 10% is available for any purchases made after attending the event. <br/>Program (approx): <br/>7.05pm Doors open. <br/>7.30pm Talk with demonstrations <br/>8.15pm Your questions. <br/>9.00pm Refreshments <br/>9.20pm Close',	'2014-11-25 20:30:00',	'2014-11-25 22:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/623496104425966/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10688398_10152435082321087_5114140392003820728_o.jpg'),
(3875,	2,	'2014-12-04T19:30:00+0000-564188267049622@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Discussion with Julian Huppert MP: How can we keep Transition issues high on the political agenda?',	'It is essential that we work on all levels to reduce climate change and increase our resilience to rising energy prices. Transition traditionally works at the level of the community, but we also need to ensurethat the government does their part. At this meeting with Cambridge\'s MP, Julian Huppert, we\'ll have the opportunity to ask him how to ensure that these issues remain high up the political agenda in central government. How can we best engage with our politicians to raise awareness about theseissues and make sure that they represent our opinions at higher levels ofgovernment? Julian will give a short talk on the this topic and then we\'ll have a chance to ask some questions and discuss the issues further. Booktickets here: <a href=\'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/transition-cambridge-with-julian-huppert-tickets-14103304363\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/transition-cambridge-with-julian-huppert-tickets-14103304363</a>  (free). More info here: <a href=\'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/transition-cambridge-with-julian-huppert-tickets-14103304363\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/transition-cambridge-with-julian-huppert-tickets-14103304363</a> ',	'2014-12-04 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/564188267049622/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/1511823_10153342334678942_2168256451758075635_o.jpg'),
(3876,	2,	'2014-12-06T12:30:00+0000-1508759339391590@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Mill Road Winter Fair',	'This December, as part of Mill Road Winter Fair, we will be meandering through Mill Road Cemetery, discussing the activity of nature through winter and exploring the significance of cemeteries for wildlife. <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of local people who want to observe local wildlife and get to know their green spaces that little bit better. <br/> <br/>All welcome (including families).   <br/>Meeting point: the Friends of Mill Road Cemetery stall in the Avenue of Limes.',	'2014-12-06 13:30:00',	'2014-12-06 14:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1508759339391590/',	'Mill Road Cemetery',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10431259_10152795374074765_1361605052493789818_o.jpg'),
(3877,	2,	'2015-01-25T11:00:00+0000-338686686316236@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Big Garden Birdwatch at Romsey Community Garden',	'For January 2015 the Nature Group will be doing their first bit of citizen science and contributing to the RSPB\'s Big Garden Birdwatch. <br/> <br/>PLEASE NOTE THE CHANGE OF TIME TO AVOID CLASH WITH SEEDY SUNDAY. <br/> <br/>11.00am - 12.00pm. <br/>We will be recording the different species of birds visiting the community garden and sending the records to the RSPB to help them with the annual winter monitoring of British bird species (Suitable for teenagers and adults).  To find out more and make records of your own gardenvisit: <a href=\'http://www.rspb.org.uk/discoverandenjoynature/discoverandlearn/birdwatch/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.rspb.org.uk/discoverandenjoynature/discoverandlearn/birdwatch/</a>  <br/> <br/>Please bring lots of warm layers and binoculars and a bird bookif you have some.  We will provide recording sheets and pencils. <br/> <br/>12.00pm - 12.30pm <br/>Come and make your own bird feeding fat balls to help feed your garden birds through the winter. (Suitable for families). <br/> <br/>All materials provided.  Small donations welcome.',	'2015-01-25 12:00:00',	'2015-01-25 13:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/338686686316236/',	'Romsey Community Garden, Marmora Road, CB1 3PY',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10623843_10152795387754765_3212847575593786082_o.jpg'),
(3878,	2,	'2015-01-27T18:30:00+0000-1398852783748558@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'TTIP  -  UNPACKED',	'Many thanks to everyone who came to our TTIP Information meeting on 27th January. This Facebook page is an event page and, to keep thisinformation visible and easy to find, I have set up another group page called TTIP - Uncovered  for everyone  to post information resources and toannounce details of future events such as meetings with MPs, MEPs etc.  <br/> <br/> <br/>As a bi-lateral trade agreement between the EU and US, TTIP is aboutreducing the regulatory barriers to trade for big businesses, in areas such as food safety law, environmental legislation, agricultural and farming standards and the sovereign powers of individual nations. However, the public and non-lobbying businesses are not being consulted at all. This meeting aims to help people to inform themselves and also to flag ways in which we can make our voices heard by decision-makers, opinion formers and the government. All welcome!',	'2015-01-27 19:30:00',	'2015-01-27 21:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1398852783748558/',	'The Earl of Beaconsfield',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/10924730_10152564894626087_5318252447133331322_n.jpg?oh=15fe6dcaccd95286823cc521bd7987c9&oe=587A5B87'),
(3879,	2,	'2015-01-29T19:30:00+0000-818246871531346@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'RE-CONOMY TRANSITION CAMBRIDGE MEETING',	'How can we fund core Transition Cambridge activities?  Is it acceptable or desirable for volunteers to earn income in a voluntary community? How can we harness the synergy of volunteer energy and experience with the vision of social entrepreneurs?  You\'re warmly invited to help us explore these and other issues around funding at this open space meeting.  It\'s free to attend, donations towards room hire costs are welcome and there are maximum 30 places available.',	'2015-01-29 20:30:00',	'2015-01-29 22:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/818246871531346/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/10389301_10152435054996087_8280222366990648573_n.jpg?oh=883c55eae0f71781c18db8f9c05c4096&oe=58394754'),
(3880,	2,	'2015-02-05T19:30:00+0000-394827540696347@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'\'Voices of Transition\' Film',	'This is the latest Transition film and focuses on local food projects. It looks really good! Please share and spread the word...  <br/>Read more here: <a href=\'http://voicesoftransition.org/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://voicesoftransition.org/</a>   <br/>There\'ll be a chance to hear about some local food projects and to chat over tea/biscuits at the end.  <br/>Cost: by donation, suggested donation approx £3-5.',	'2015-02-05 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/394827540696347/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/10945010_10153549201743942_2018076710195258405_n.jpg?oh=ea6890f4fb34385e58e9ca93c827589c&oe=587D28D1'),
(3881,	2,	'2015-02-22T11:15:00+0000-340097622840455@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Paradise LNR',	'Come and join us for a wintery walk along the Cam, through Paradise LNR.   We last visited Paradise in August 2013!!!  So now a chance to observe this beautiful riverside spot in the depths of chilly period. <br/> <br/>Wildlife Wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of local residents who want to get to know there local green spaces that little bit better.  We simply get together to observe what is happening in our urban wilderness\' and to share any knowledge that we have. <br/> <br/>11:15 for a 11:30 start - until 12:45. <br/> <br/>Meeting point:  The Ice Cream kiosk, next to the Lidoon Lammas Land.   <br/> <br/>Please bring walking/ welly boots (we\'re expecting lots of mud) and lots of warm layers of clothing.  <br/> <br/>All welcome: including dogs and families.',	'2015-02-22 12:15:00',	'2015-02-22 13:45:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/340097622840455/',	'Paradise LNR',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/10980169_10152985633764765_125043885378795491_o.jpg'),
(3882,	2,	'2015-03-02T19:30:00+0000-1591772121041116@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'THE SOCIAL COST OF CARBON - with Michael Grubb',	'Many of us are making changes in our lives towards a low carbon world, but to make this happen on a wider scale we need serious, hard-hitting economic measures too. What are the options, how do they work, and are they practical in the real world? Join us for a discussion and Q/A session to find the most effective and practical solutions.   <br/>Michael Grubb is Professor of International Energy and Climate Change Policy at UCL and a senior advisor to Ofgem and is the author of  Planetary Economics.',	'2015-03-02 20:30:00',	'2015-03-02 22:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1591772121041116/',	'Friends Meeting House, Jesus Lane, CB5 8BA',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/10447800_10152626850846087_5000140842045152523_n.jpg?oh=5eb40dd6fe8d1687dd25321549a8d135&oe=587E96ED'),
(3883,	2,	'2015-03-06T17:15:00+0000-1561966460724773@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Meeting with Julian Huppert about TTIP',	'The TC Food Group has arranged a surgery meeting with Julian Huppert to ask questions and register our concerns about TTIP. We plan to question him about the environmental impact, food safety and food labelling implications of TTIP,  as well as the fundamental conflict between increasing opportunities for global trade which directly affects reliance on and increased use of fossil fuel energy.  There\'s also interest in asking about ISDS,  the NHS and employee rights as well.  It would be great to get a few of us along for more impact, If you\'d like to join us, please message Jacky Sutton-Adam so we can keep an eye on numbers.',	'2015-03-06 18:15:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1561966460724773/',	'The Guildhall',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/11021141_10152644277021087_8754408645681265784_n.jpg?oh=25b62495b5d33260ffe542f0caa9d06d&oe=583A94E1'),
(3884,	2,	'2015-03-20T19:30:00+0000-1565327567079202@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Environment and Climate Change Question Time (i.e. Hustings!)',	'Do you wish politicians would listen to your views on the environment and sustainability? Not sure how to vote? Come to this free event and put your questions to Cambridgeâ€™s parliamentary candidates, with Dr Aled Jones in the chair to ensure fair play and a good debate. Informal discussions can continue afterwards. The following parliamentary candidates will be present: Chamali Fernando (Conservative), Julian Huppert (Lib Dem), Rupert Read (Green) and Daniel Zeichner (Labour). Dr Aled Jones is Director of the Global Sustainability Institute at Anglia Ruskin University. <br/> <br/>BOOKING desirable, but not essential: <a href=\'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/cambridge-environment-climate-change-question-time-tickets-15153000031\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/cambridge-environment-climate-change-question-time-tickets-15153000031</a>  <br/> <br/>Here\'s the poster if you\'re able to put it up somewhere - thanks!  <a href=\'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/cambridge-environment-climate-change-question-time-tickets-15153000031\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/cambridge-environment-climate-change-question-time-tickets-15153000031</a>    <br/> <br/>This event is free.  <br/> <br/>Organised by Transition Cambridge and Cambridge Carbon Footprint, with support from Anglia Ruskin University.',	'2015-03-20 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1565327567079202/',	'Lord Ashcroft International Business School, Anglia Ruskin University East Road CB1 1PT (Main entrance)',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/11051803_10153664620263942_2357644022113279654_o.jpg'),
(3885,	2,	'2015-03-21T11:15:00+0000-796667873721746@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings - Cherry Hinton Chalk Pits',	'I couldn\'t believe it when I realised Wildlife Wanderings havn\'t visited Cherry Hinton Chalk Pits.  This SSSI (Site of Special Scientific Interest) is home to glow worms and the rare Moon Carrot and there are even historic records of Charles Darwin visiting the neighbouring Lime KilnClose. <br/> <br/>Join us for a walk around this seemingly barren landscape to discuss the role that human activity has on creating opportunities for nature, and the importance of chalk habitats.  <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is a friendly and informal gathering of local residents who want to get to know their local green spaces better.  We simply get together to wander round a local nature reserve or park and make observations of our surroundings, sharing any knowledge we have. <br/> <br/>Wildlife wanderings is free and open to all.  Families and dogs are welcome.  <br/> <br/>Meet at Cherry Hinton Chalk Pits entrance.  11.15am for an 11.30am start. <br/> <br/>Please bring sturdy shoes and warm clothes. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.wildlifebcn.org/reserves/cherry-hinton\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.wildlifebcn.org/reserves/cherry-hinton</a> ',	'2015-03-21 12:15:00',	'2015-03-21 13:45:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/796667873721746/',	'Cherry Hinton Chalk Pit Nature Reserve',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/11025879_10153037412214765_1948191655900244907_o.jpg'),
(3886,	2,	'2015-03-24T18:30:00+0000-1545864702345835@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Fermented Foods Skillshare',	'Join us for this reminder or intro evening we\'ll discuss some common worries and problems with home fermentation and make a batch of fermented kraut together. Please bring a chopping board and kitchen knife you\'re comfortable using, a jam jar or small kilner (no bigger than .75L please!) If you have books or resources to share bring them along. Veg will be provided, this event is free but we ask for a small donation towards the cost of ingredients and room hire. All welcome, no fermenting experience necessary! Book with me via pm so we can manage numbers - thanks',	'2015-03-24 19:30:00',	'2015-03-24 21:15:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1545864702345835/',	'Ross Street Community Centre',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3887,	2,	'2015-05-16T14:00:00+0100-1587659138179549@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Cambridge\'s 2nd Repair Cafe',	'A chance to get your broken items repaired. We have volunteerswho can mend bikes, books, jewellery, clothes, gadgets, electricals, computers and more. No guarantees but we\'ll do our best, or point you towards a professional repairer or a spares supplier. Free event (with cake!). Donations welcome to cover venue costs. Book via Transition Cambridge website, or come along on the day and we\'ll try to fit you in.',	'2015-05-16 15:00:00',	'2015-05-16 18:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1587659138179549/',	'St Andrews Hall, Chesterton, CB4 1DH',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3888,	2,	'2015-07-07T19:30:00+0100-1466609290316139@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'\'Seek the Change\' talk with Emily Dunning',	'Emily Dunning has just returned from a 6-month trip travellingoverland via the Trans-Mongolian Expressway to China, and then via several more countries to New Zealand. During her travels she met up with various people working on sustainability initiatives, from youth climate action groups in Taiwan to clean-up events in Russia to the social enterprise ethos inspiring change in Japan. She\'ll tell us about the joys and challenges of such a long overland journey, and the inspiration she took from themany sustainability projects she visited along the way. To find out more about what she\'s been up to, have a look at her blog seekthechange.org. Free, all welcome. If you\'d like to help out with the cafe, please get intouch!',	'2015-07-07 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1466609290316139/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/11659242_10153980821868942_7875924849258723517_n.jpg?oh=6cb5f2badfa6e962c97a8a1c03fd56f0&oe=586F8744'),
(3889,	2,	'2015-07-22T19:30:00+0100-684681318332569@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Film: \'Pollinating Change\' with the Buzz Tour',	'\'Pollinating Change\' follows the Buzz Tour on a 1,300 mile walk around England, camping and living off donations. The Bees (Eve and friends) interviewed over 80 people about the inspiring things they were doing to change our culture not climate. As they wrestle with the day to day difficulties of food and shelter they explore the range of tactics being used to collectively reduce climate change and the different journeys of personal change. Come along to meet Eve as she passes through Cambridge (sheis now travelling by bicycle). Find out more about the Buzz Tour here: <a href=\'http://buzztour.org/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://buzztour.org/</a> ',	'2015-07-22 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/684681318332569/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3890,	2,	'2015-09-19T11:00:00+0100-1485586335069876@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Wildlife Wanderings: Nine Wells Nature Reserve nr Addenbrooke\'s Hospital',	'Nine Wells is one of Cambridge City Councilâ€™s Local Nature Reserves, and the source of Hobsonâ€™s Conduit! Close to Addenbrookeâ€™s hospital, it can be seen from the train as you head south of the city. Weâ€™ll do a circuit from Red Cross Lane to the reserve and follow the footpaths to the Babraham Park & Ride. Nine Wells has woodland, springs and a chalk stream. Weâ€™ll be looking at hedgerow fruits and berries and other signs of autumn and talking about their importance to birds and other wildlife. Weâ€™llalso be talking about foraging, so come prepared with bags!',	'2015-09-19 12:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1485586335069876/',	'Meet by the Bell School, Red Cross Lane CB2 0QU',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/q86/s720x720/11891459_171337773199252_5879578878480217982_o.jpg'),
(3891,	2,	'2015-09-28T00:00:00+0100-403756023165402@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Getting to the Heart of Permaculture Design',	'A course offered by Wendy Seabrook from Hill Top Farm in Australia. This is a four day course, offered very cheaply as it is a new course that Wendy is developing. Full details and booking here: <a href=\'http://www.transitioncambridge.org/heartofpermaculturedesign.\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.transitioncambridge.org/heartofpermaculturedesign.</a>   <br/> <br/>Permaculture at its heart is a design process, where the main focus is creating productive and regenerative systems for both us and our environment. This course providesparticipants with the skills to interpret and put into action a toolkit of the Key Ecological Practices. We have developed these Ecological Practices to help people redesign their systems to better mimic the functioning of healthy natural ecosystems. The Ecological Practices are universally applicable for different climates and ventures, and not centered on principles needing translating into practical tools, before they are accessible. <br/> <br/>Read more here: <a href=\'http://www.transitioncambridge.org/heartofpermaculturedesign.\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.transitioncambridge.org/heartofpermaculturedesign.</a> ',	'2015-09-28 01:00:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/403756023165402/',	'Cambridge Sustainability Centre',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	''),
(3892,	2,	'2016-01-30T13:30:00+0000-474912246047690@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Cambridge Repair Cafe',	'Do you like fixing things? Or maybe you have something that needs fixing?  <br/> <br/>Come along to the Cambridge Repair Cafe on 30 January and you can do either - or both!  <br/> <br/>Repair Cafes are a chance to get broken items repaired and teach or learn simple repair skills. <br/> <br/>Our volunteers can tackle repairs of bikes, jewellery, clean clothes, gadgets, electricals, computers and more. No guarantees but we\'ll do our best, or point you towards a professional repairer or a spares supplier.  <br/> <br/>Donations are welcome to cover venue costs. Free entry.  <br/>Tea and cakes available. <br/> <br/>More details and booking at transitioncambridge.org/repaircafe.   <br/> <br/>Please book your item in advance by Sat 23 Jan if possible. If you come along on the day we\'ll do our best to fit you in. <br/> <br/>Everyone\'s welcome and we\'reespecially keen to hear from new repairers, so please get in touch.',	'2016-01-30 14:30:00',	'2016-01-30 17:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/474912246047690/',	'St Andrew\'s Hall, Chesterton, Cambridge CB4 1DH',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/12615731_935411769860626_5951319041169313517_o.jpg'),
(3893,	2,	'2016-02-03T19:30:00+0000-967225140028305@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Film: Water Blues, Green Solutions',	'A new Transition group is forming, looking at how we can staydry when faced with changes in climate and increased rainfall. At this first event, we will show \'Water Blues, Green Solutions\'. This film illustrates small-scale solutions implemented by local groups in four American cities, inspiring bottom-up actions to localised flood prevention. We hopeto form an action group that can implement small-scale bottom-up solutions to localised flood prevention in Cambridge. Come along to find our more!All welcome, free (by donation). For more information, see the new \'Learning to Stay Dry\' webpage here: <a href=\'http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTStayingDry.HomePage.\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTStayingDry.HomePage.</a>  See here for more info on thefilm:  <a href=\'http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTStayingDry.HomePage.\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.transitioncambridge.org/thewiki/ttwiki/pmwiki.php?n=TTStayingDry.HomePage.</a> ',	'2016-02-03 20:30:00',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/967225140028305/',	'Friends Meeting House',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/s720x720/12573157_10154475700598942_489326185707776729_n.jpg?oh=09c664e057f0e5e6f0f0d4e532ecfae7&oe=5843CACA'),
(3894,	2,	'2016-06-09T19:15:00+0100-1732007980380474@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Conversation Cafe on the EU Referendum',	'Our Conversation Cafe, organised in association with our friends at Pivotal, is an opportunity to create some space in which to hear and be heard. The evening will be a mixture of facilitated group discussionaround Transition and Pivotal values, such as the environment, social justice and democracy, food and water security, energy security and immigration. The aim is simply to help people find some personal clarity about their voting position. No party political speeches, grandstanding or attempts to sway opinion, just honest conversation with refreshments. This event is free, with a suggested on the door donation of £3 -£5 but please register at <a href=\'http://bit.ly/EUConversation\' target=\'_blank\'>http://bit.ly/EUConversation</a>  lookig forward to seeing you there!',	'2016-06-09 20:15:00',	'2016-06-09 23:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1732007980380474/',	'Unitarian Church Emmanuel Road Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/s720x720/13235224_10153500135571087_3569003812538664071_o.jpg'),
(3895,	2,	'2016-07-02T13:30:00+0100-661761203989802@hubcal.axwax.uk',	'Cambridge Repair Cafe',	'Cambridge Repair Cafe is back! <br/> <br/>Your opportunity to get a broken item repaired and to pick  up some repair skills. Experienced volunteer repairers can help with your faulty laptops, bikes, small household appliances, sewing and jewellery repairs, CD players etc.  <br/> <br/>We will do our best, but can\'t guarantee we can fix everything.  <br/> <br/>We still have a few spaces, so please book as soon as possible preferably via the Transition Cambridge website.  <br/> <br/>Great cakes and tea available in our cafe area.It\'s a free event, but we welcome donations to cover venue hire and printing costs. If you\'d like to help out (set up, meet and greet, in the kitchen, clear up) please let us know.',	'2016-07-02 14:30:00',	'2016-07-02 17:30:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/661761203989802/',	'St Andrews Hall, Chesterton, CB4 1DH',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/t31.0-8/q83/s720x720/13475174_1029428143792321_5467001086305368770_o.jpg'),
