(16883,	4,	'3538-1453906800-1453919400@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Cambridge Sustainable Food Fair for Businesses',	'This drop-in event, intended for food businesses and suppliers, will see the launch of Cambridge Sustainable Foodâ€™s Pledge for Food Businesses, which is linked to our Sustainable Food Charter. <br/> <br/>There will be a talk about food sustainability by Andrew Balmford, Professor of Conservation Science at the Department of Zoology, University of Cambridge and a chance to meet various people who can explain what it would mean to fulfil different aspects of the new food pledge, such as food procurement, health, environmental sustainability, supporting local businesses and food fairness. There will also be stalls where local food suppliers can display their wares. <br/> <br/>  <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>  <br/> <br/>Programme for Cambridge Sustainable Food Fair for Businesses 27th January <br/>Lloyd Room, Christâ€™s College, St Andrewâ€™s Street, Cambridge CB2 3BU <br/> <br/>3.00     Event opens â€“ stalls available to browse, with people to talk to about different aspects of the sustainable food pledge <br/> <br/>3.10      Introduction to the Cambridge Sustainable Food Pledge, Duncan Catchpole, Cambridge Sustainable Food and CEO of Cambridge Organic Food Company, who will also give a brief talk on the Cambridge Sustainable Food Hub project <br/> <br/>3.40    The environmental impact of food and some ideas for lowering it, overview and discussion with Andrew Balmford and Erasmus zu Ermgassen, Dept of Zoology <br/> <br/>3.50     Environmental Sustainability - Sustainable Fish Cities, Ruth Westcott, Sustain <br/> <br/>3.55     Environmental Sustainability - ARUâ€™s Green Eating Award, Sami Whitaker <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>4.00     Time to visit the stalls and get information from experts on particular aspects of the pledge <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>4.45     Food Fairness â€“ The Living Wage, Theresa Bateman, Cambridge City Councilâ€™s Living Wage Coordinator <br/> <br/>4.50     Food Fairness â€“ Fairtrade, Paul Gans of the Cambridge Fairtrade Committee <br/> <br/>4.55     Cambridge City Council Commercial Food Waste Collection Service, Greg Hutton-Squire <br/> <br/>5.00     Healthier Options, Frank Harrison, Cambridge City Council <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>5.00     Time to visit the stalls and get information from experts on particular aspects of the pledge <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>6.30     Event ends <br/> <br/>  <br/> <br/>Local suppliersâ€™ stalls: <br/> <br/>    Hodmedodâ€™s, Bressingham, Diss, suppliers of British-grown peas, beans and quinoa <br/>    Cobâ€™s Bakery, Cambridge <br/>    Radwinter Wild Game, Saffron Walden <br/> <br/>Pledge information stalls, with experts to answer your questions: <br/> <br/>    Cambridge Sustainable Food Pledge, Sam Dyer <br/>    Cambridge Food Hub Project, Duncan Catchpole <br/>    Sustainable Fish Cities, Ruth Westcott <br/>    ARU Green Eating Scheme, Sami Whitaker <br/>    Fairtrade, Paul Gans <br/>    The Living Wage, Theresa Bateman <br/>    City Council Commercial Food Waste Collection Scheme, Greg Hutton-Squire <br/> <br/>  <br/> <br/>It is best to go to the Portersâ€™ Lodge on St Andrewâ€™s Street (on the corner of St Andrewâ€™s Street and Hobson Street) and ask for directions to The Lloyd Room, which is in the far corner of the Third Court. <br/> <br/>Please contact Bev at <a href=\"mailto:bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org\">bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org</a> if you are a food business interested in attending.',	'2016-01-27 15:00:00',	'2016-01-27 18:30:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/cambridge-sustainable-food-fair-for-businesses/',	'Christ\'s College, St Andrew\'s St, Cambridge, CB2 3BU, United Kingdom',	'2016-01-18 16:44:11',	'',	'',	''),
(16884,	4,	'3541-1454151600-1454169600@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Volunteer for Cambridge',	'Cambridge Sustainable Food will have a stall at the Hub\'s \'Volunteer for Cambridge\' fair. Come along to find out more about what we do, the volunteering opportunities we have to offer and what it\'s like to work with CSF. We look forward to meeting you! <br/> <br/>We will also need volunteers on the day to help out with running the stall. Get in touch if are able to help out, even for a short time: <a href=\"mailto:bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org\">bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org</a> <br/> <br/>More details about the Cambridge Hub event can be found here and you can join the Facebook event here.',	'2016-01-30 11:00:00',	'2016-01-30 16:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/volunteer-for-cambridge/',	'Market Swaure, Cambridge, CB2 3QJ',	'2015-12-07 11:17:02',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hubvolunteer.jpg'),
(16885,	4,	'2710-1460541600-1460548800@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Fullspoon Healthy Eating Course - St. Paul\'s Cambridge',	'A free healthy eating course delivered by GAP Learning CIC <br/>Fullspoon by GAP Learning CIC is now looking for recruits â€“ if you love cooking and want to learn some delicious healthy recipes that you can share with friends and family, then look no further. Enrolments are now being accepted for the Autumn term courses. Click here to download an enrolment form from the GAP Learning CIC Website. <br/> <br/>The Fullspoon course aims to teach learners how to cook delicious healthy low-cost meals. All ingredients are provided and there is also a possibility of gaining a food hygiene certificate. Simple recipes are completed each week with a variety of areas including cultural meals, herbs and spices and seasonal goods. The lessons culminate in all the learners and staff sitting down together and sharing the food. Children are encouraged to come for lunch when appropriate. Fullspoon also takes into account the produce that is available in food banks and these staples are included in the recipes. <br/>This is a five week free course beginning Wednesday 13th April 10am-12pm and continuing at the same time and location for the following five weeks. See below for a week by week lesson plan. <br/> <br/>Learn practical skills and some fantastic recipes for some healthy, homely foods such as lasagne and soup. This course is intended to give you the knowledge and confidence to cook great meals at home or even maybe start your own business in the catering field. <br/> <br/>Week 1: Cooking with potatoes and fresh fruit & vegetables  <br/> <br/>Week 2: Simple Soups & Bread <br/> <br/>Week 3: Cooking with mince <br/> <br/>Week 4: Cooking with chicken <br/> <br/>Week 5: Ready Steady Cook challenge <br/> <br/>(Dietary requirements and allergies will be taken into consideration) <br/> <br/>If you require more information or have any questions get in touch with Amanda or Teresa at Gap Learning CIC by email <a href=\"mailto:gaplearning@gmail.com\">gaplearning@gmail.com</a> or phone 01480 731131 or Alex <a href=\"mailto:alex@stpaulscambridge.org.uk\">alex@stpaulscambridge.org.uk</a> <br/> <br/>GAP Learning can also be found on Facebook and Twitter.',	'2016-04-13 10:00:00',	'2016-04-13 12:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/fullspoon-healthy-eating-course-st-pauls-cambridge/',	'Hills Road, Cambridge, CB2 1JP',	'2015-09-01 15:05:41',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/fullspoon.jpg'),
(16886,	5,	'2016-01-17T19:00:00+0000-749359175195791@green-calendar.gigx.co.uk',	'Ethical Network Lent Term Gathering',	'\'This is a great opportunity for you to learn more about the Hub. We will look back on exciting events we held in Michaelmas and introduce to you all the supportive events that we run for you in the new term. You can also gain hugely by meeting societies with similar initiatives and co-host events with them! Lastly, you can publise your society in a largenetwork with over 60+ societies!\' <br/> <br/>Anyone with a genuine interest in ethical issues is also welcome to attend! RSVP to <a href=\"mailto:network@cambridgehub.org\">network@cambridgehub.org</a> to confirm your attendance :) <br/> <br/>Categories including: <br/>-Umbrella Groups for Social & Environmental Action in Cambridge <br/>-Environment: Energy, Sustainability & Investments <br/>-Environment: Conservation <br/>-Environment- EthicalConsumerism <br/>-Environment- Food Waste & Food Shortage <br/>-Education <br/>-Homelessness <br/>-Health & Wellbeing <br/>-International Volunteering <br/>-International Campaigning <br/> <br/> <br/>See full list of member societies, please visit: <a href=\'http://www.cambridgehub.org/ethical-network\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.cambridgehub.org/ethical-network</a> ',	'2016-01-17 19:00:00',	'2016-01-17 21:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/749359175195791/',	'Keynes Hall, King\'s College',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xft1/t31.0-0/p180x540/12493643_787223758050784_303990748707336244_o.jpg'),
(16887,	5,	'2016-01-22T19:15:00+0000-1546145679035710@green-calendar.gigx.co.uk',	'*TONIGHT*Stolen Title: Genocide, Massacres, and Asylum',	'A night of poetry and music from Iraqi-Assyrian poet Nineb Lamassu and folk artist Helen Saint Vincent.  <br/> <br/>We are very proud to host Nineb Lamassu, an Iraqi-Assyrian poet from the Faculty of Asian and Middle Eastern Studies, who will be joined by Helen Saint Vincent, an Iranian-Assyrian active feminist and a folk artist from Cologne, Germany.  <br/> <br/>Nineb Lamassu will be reading poems from his new collection, which deal with some of the most pressing issues in the world today. Through his work, Nineb explores issues surrounding the genocide of 1915 which was perpetuatedagainst the Assyrian, Armenians and the Greeks of the Ottoman Empire, as well as more topical affairs, such as the takeover by ISIS\' of large areas of Syria and Iraq, and ISIS\' atrocities against the people of region, especially the indigenous people - the Yezidies and the Assyrians.  <br/> <br/>Helen Saint Vincent will perform, a capella, some of the most thought provoking and emotional Assyrian folk songs dealing with genocide and massacre.  <br/> <br/>The evening will also allocate a Q and A session <br/> <br/>This event willbe free, with a collection for the Cambridge Hub. <br/> <br/>Sure to be an interesting event for anyone interested in poetry, music, or the Middle East.',	'2016-01-22 19:15:00',	'1970-01-01 01:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1546145679035710/',	'Keynes Hall, Kings College',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpt1/t31.0-0/p180x540/12471377_789992137773946_4027786701573774197_o.jpg'),
(16888,	5,	'2016-01-30T11:00:00+0000-854991341288386@green-calendar.gigx.co.uk',	'Volunteer for Cambridge',	'Book a free ticket here (<a href=\'http://volunteerforcambridge.eventbrite.com/?aff=facebook)\' target=\'_blank\'>http://volunteerforcambridge.eventbrite.com/?aff=facebook)</a>  to be entered into prize draw! <br/> <br/>Volunteer for Cambridge is your one-stop shop for finding out how to get involved in the causes you care about, give something back and gain skills.  <br/> <br/>Building on the success of last year\'s event, which saw almost 600 people through thedoors and over 80 organisations represented, we\'re gearing up to deliveran even bigger, even bigger day.  <br/> <br/>Hosted by Cambridge City Council & Cambridge Hub, Volunteer for Cambridge is a city-wide fair bringing together organisations in the Cambridge community who work to create positive social and environmental change through volunteering. The fair will featurea marketplace of charities, voluntary organisations and student societies, as well as a kids area and a cafe.  <br/> <br/>Confirm your attendance for Volunteer for Cambridge today by registering on evenbrite for free via the link above. There\'s no need to book in advance if you\'d rather just drop by on the day, but those who register for the event will be entered into theprize draw to win one of these fantastic prizes when you come along on the day: <br/>- A £500 voucher to spend at University Cycles <br/>- 3 months Gym membership <br/>- £100 Corn Exchange Voucher <br/>- Dinner & wine at Camb Events February Popup at Sticky Beaks (<a href=\'http://volunteerforcambridge.eventbrite.com/?aff=facebook)\' target=\'_blank\'>http://volunteerforcambridge.eventbrite.com/?aff=facebook)</a>  <br/> <br/>A full list of this year\'s stall-holders can be seen at www.cambridgehub.org/volunteer-for-cambridge.',	'2016-01-30 11:00:00',	'2016-01-30 16:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/854991341288386/',	'The Guildhall, Market Square, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpf1/t31.0-8/s720x720/10296474_777958048977355_8241200721282358659_o.jpg'),
(16889,	5,	'2016-02-01T21:00:00+0000-1675886566030692@green-calendar.gigx.co.uk',	'SPEAK FOR ACTION: Open Mic Night in Aid of Refugee Action',	'CAMBRIDGE HUB PRESENTS: Speak for Action!  <br/>A new series of spoken word/performance art around the theme of \'Home\'.  <br/>Please bring alonganything you\'d like to perform- self-written or otherwise- and help us raise money for Refugee Action and Cambridge Hub. <br/>Post your name on the wall if you\'d like to perform. £3 entry (including performers).  <br/>See you there! <br/>Cambridge Hub',	'2016-02-01 21:00:00',	'2016-02-01 23:00:00',	'https://www.facebook.com/events/1675886566030692/',	'Clare College Cellars',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xta1/t31.0-8/q86/s720x720/12525610_792892074150619_573340881623045057_o.jpg'),
(16890,	6,	'12279-1453893300-1453899600@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Medsin Talk: The Impact of Depression on Society',	'Professor Peter Jones will be talking to us about the impact of depression on society, an important topic, which will be of particular interest to medics and those who wish to learn more about psychiatric disorders. Come along to what should be a fascinating talk! Food and drink will be provided.',	'2016-01-27 11:15:00',	'2016-01-27 13:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/medsin-talk-the-impact-of-depression-on-society/',	'Caius College, Cambridge',	'2016-01-13 14:59:17',	'',	'',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/MedisonCambridge.png'),
