(16912,	22,	'e1545112625803322@facebook.com',	'TODAY: Vegan Potluck Party!',	'Join us on Saturday 23rd January at Clare College Gatehouse for a glorious vegan feast, where you bring the dishes! <br/> <br/>Cambridge University Vegan Society, with the kind collaboration of Clare Vegans, is once more holding their ever popularsocial event, the Vegan Potluck Party! <br/> <br/>For those unfamilar with the term \"Potluck\", this is simply afood-sharing party, where every guest brings a dish of (vegan) foodto share, and gets to share everyone else\'s in return! <br/>NB! If you can, bring a plate, cutlery, a cup etc. (we will try to provide a fewpaper plates and plastic cutlery in case someone cannot bring theirown). <br/> <br/>Suggestions for what to bring: fruit, veg curry, carrot sticks, hummus, crackers, bread rolls,drinks, crisps, bourbons, oreos, vegan cake, stuffed mushrooms, sosrolls, tofu rashers, sheese topped pizza, veg pates, vegan chocolate, pasta dishes, risotto, veg tarts, vegan brownies... <br/> <br/>As always, there is no need to be vegan or even vegetarian to attend our events.Everyone is welcome! <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/events/1545112625803322/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.facebook.com/events/1545112625803322/</a> ',	'2016-01-23 13:00:00',	'2016-01-23 16:00:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/1545112625803322/',	'The Gatehouse @ Clare College, Memorial Court, Queens\' Road',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Jo Humphrey',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
(16913,	28,	'e809883372474632@facebook.com',	'TODAY - Your perfect career â€“ does volunteering help you get there?',	'Come and find out about your future career in the Civil Service, management consultancy and the ThirdSector. <br/> <br/>When: 7pm, 23rd January <br/>Where: Latimer Room, Clare CollegeOld Court <br/> <br/>Our three panel members from DFID, Deloitte and the charity sector will talk about their journeys into their current careersand the role of volunteering within this. They will also provide careers guidance and an insight intotheir day-to-day life in their current job. This will be followed by a Q&A session, and then a more general informal chit-chat. <br/> <br/>Drinksand nibbles will be provided. <br/> <br/>THE SPEAKERS: <br/> <br/>Fiona studied undergraduate Geography at Cambridge University. She is currently the Programme Manager for DFIDâ€™s Yemen operations. She has worked in DFID for almost 4 years, managing the humanitarian and governance programmes in Yemen and providing analytical support to the Africa portfolio. She is also in her second year of part-time study for a Masters indisaster risk reduction and climate change adaptation, with specific focus on social protection systems. She has been involved with EPAfrica for a number of years and formerly sat on the charityâ€™s Management Committee. <br/> <br/>Luke read MML, and is now a Manager at Deloitte, within the Consulting practice. Luke specialises in supporting organisations within the Public Sector to transform the way they operate driven by financial, political andefficiency pressures. He has alsovolunteered with EPAfrica over the last ten years and has used thisexperience to help his career progression. <br/> <br/>Jessica studied undergraduate Geography at Cambridge University. She currently works for The Scout Association as an Operations Adviser for Adult Training. Herrole is to help adult volunteers in undertaking their roles throughproducing and supporting the delivery of training within the Movement. Jessica has volunteered with EPAfrica for the past 4 years and is currently a member of the charityâ€™s Management Committee. The skills and experiences she has gained from volunteering with EPAfrica have been instrumental in the progression of her career. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/events/809883372474632/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.facebook.com/events/809883372474632/</a> ',	'2016-01-23 19:00:00',	'2016-01-23 22:00:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/809883372474632/',	'Latimer Room, Clare College Old Court',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'EPAfrica Cambridge and ARU',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
