(17941,	27,	'e952440918183364@facebook.com',	'Narrative Medicine',	'\'The care of the sick unfolds in stories. The effective practice ofhealthcare requires the ability to recognize, absorb, interpret, and act on the stories and plights of others. Medicine practiced with narrative competence is a model for humane and effective medical practice.\'  <br/> <br/>We are delighted to welcome Dr. John Launer to Cambridge. Dr. Launer studied medicine after completing an undergraduate degreein English here in Cambridge. He is a doctor, family therapist, educator and award-winning writer.  <br/> <br/>He is an honorary lifetime consultant at the Tavistock Clinic, honorary senior lecturer at Queen Mary University of London, and associate dean at Health Education England. <br/> <br/>Dr. Launer will talk to us about his experience writing about andpracticing narrative medicine. All are welcome. There will be plenty of time for questions and discussion afterwards. <br/> <br/>Last year Dr. Launer published a biography of the phsyciatrist Sabina Spielrein and he will be happy to take questionson this also. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/events/952440918183364/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.facebook.com/events/952440918183364/</a> ',	'2016-02-02 19:30:00',	'2016-02-02 22:30:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/952440918183364/',	'Keynes\' Hall, Kings College, Cambridge',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Deana Gershuny',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
