(19645,	21,	'e227046387630087@facebook.com',	'The Age of Stupid - Presented by KCSU & Zero Carbon',	'A film screening joint-hosted by KCSU & Zero Carbon to celebrate the start of Go Green Week. <br/> <br/>You cansign Zero Carbon\'s petition asking the university to divest from fossil fuels here; <a href=\'https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179\' target=\'_blank\'>https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179</a>  <br/> <br/>About thefilm - <br/>\"A future archivist looks at old footage from the early 21st-century to understand why humankind failed to address climate change.\" <br/> <br/>Combining drama, documentary and animation, \'The Age of Stupid\'explores our reluctance to face up to climate change, and the devastating consequences - giving a human face to a worldwide tragedy. <br/> <br/>Trailer; <br/><a href=\'https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179\' target=\'_blank\'>https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179</a>  <br/> <br/>\"It\'s a sort ofdrama-documentary, but I promise it\'s worth watching. It stars PetePostlethwaite, who was a wonderful, wonderful man for a whole host of reasons. <br/> <br/>Don\'t be put off by the title - the film does a pretty good job of asking why we\'re so bad at doing something about climatechange, and getting across the human impact of such a huge, faceless crisis. <br/> <br/>It has laughs - an englishman asking someone about glaciers in absolutely appalling French never fails to make me chuckle - and some light hearted animation. But that doesn\'t detract from the dark side of the film - as well as resource conflict in the Middle East, it shines a light on the horrific treatment of Nigerians by Shell - an issue which definitely deserves more widespread internationalattention - and the damage already done by climate change to communities around the world.\" <br/> - Chris,KCSU Green & Charities <br/> <br/><a href=\'https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179\' target=\'_blank\'>https://campaigns.gofossilfree.org/petitions/cambridge-university-divest-from-fossil-fuels-1?time=1446419179</a> ',	'2016-02-07 20:00:00',	'2016-02-07 21:30:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/227046387630087/',	'Keynes Hall',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Chris Galpin',	'christopher.galpin.guernesey@googlemail.com',	''),
(19957,	4,	'3663-1455040800-1455048000@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Cambridge Soup: eat, share, vote.',	'Launched by Allia and supported by the Future Business Centre Cambridge,  \'Cambridge Soup\' is a platform to enable micro-crowdfunding for community projects. The idea is simple: everyone pays £5 on the door, and eats together while four different organisations present their projects. There will be a chance for questions and discussion, and at the end, everyone votes for the project they think the collections should go to. Find out more on the event website here.',	'2016-02-09 18:00:00',	'2016-02-09 20:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/cambridge-soup-eat-share-vote/',	'47 Norfolk St, Cambridge, CB1 2LD, United Kingdom',	'2016-02-01 16:56:45',	'',	'',	''),
