(20988,	4,	'3671-1457553600-1457557200@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Eating less meat: government policy or your choice? at the Cambridge Science Festival',	'If current trends continue, shifts in global tastes towards Western diets coupled with population growth are predicted to double meat production by 2050. These changes will not only influence peopleâ€™s health, they will also impact the environment. A panel will explore both the arguments surrounding reduced meat consumption and the role that policy could and should play in changing what people eat. <br/> <br/>This event is being co-hosted by the Cambridge Forum for Sustainability and the Environment and the Cambridge Public Policy Strategic Research Initiative. <br/> <br/> ',	'2016-03-09 20:00:00',	'2016-03-09 21:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/eating-less-meat-government-policy-or-your-choice-at-the-cambridge-science-festival/',	'8 Mill Lane, cb2 1rw, United Kingdom',	'2016-02-03 09:25:19',	'',	'',	''),
