(29215,	22,	'e576215235874244@facebook.com',	'Green Open Space- Cooperation',	'This term\'s Green Open Space willbe focused on collaboration and connection. This discussion will begreat for diverse people and groups in Cambridge to find what they have in common, and think about how they can together support a transition to sustainable living. The Open Space events are open to anyone who is involved in environmental work: campaigning, policy, education, etc. <br/> <br/>The floor will be veryopen and there is no set agenda, but only a light facilitation allowing the conversation to be about the topics the participants want to talk about! If you haven\'t heardabout Open Spaces before, this iswhat Wikipedia says: <br/> <br/>â€œOpen Space is the only process that focuses on expanding time and space for the force of self-organisation to do its thing. Although one can\'t predict specific outcomes, it\'s always highly productive for whateverissue people want to attend to. Some of the inspiring side effects that are regularly noted are laughter, hard work which feels like play, surprising results and fascinating new questionsâ€ <br/> <br/>Come along and bring your friends, smiles andideas! <br/> <br/>Please RSVP and send any questions to Laura at <a href=\"mailto:environment@cambridgehub.org\">environment@cambridgehub.org</a>. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/events/576215235874244/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.facebook.com/events/576215235874244/</a> ',	'2016-03-02 19:15:00',	'2016-03-02 21:00:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/576215235874244/',	'Harrods Room, Emmanuel College',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Cambridge Hub',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
(29220,	23,	'e518360771622356@facebook.com',	'Dr Andy Clements: Wildlife interactions with the landscape',	'Wildlife interactions with the landscape: BTO research at global tolocal scales <br/> <br/>From tracking Cuckoos to their wintering grounds in Africa, to \"citizen science\" projects here in the UK, come find out about the amazing work of the British Trust for Ornithology from its Director, Dr. Andy Clements. The BTO is a charitable research institute aimed at using evidence to inform conservation practice and environmental policy, particularly in relation to birdlife. <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/events/518360771622356/\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.facebook.com/events/518360771622356/</a> ',	'2016-03-02 19:00:00',	'2016-03-02 22:00:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/518360771622356/',	'Seminar Room, David Attenborough Building (New Museums Site)',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Cambridge University Nature Society',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
