(34341,	4,	'3837-1463472000-1463504400@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'What IS the deal with meat? Cambridge Carbon Footprint @ Eat festival',	'Thereâ€™s been a lot of media attention around the impact of meat on our health and the environment. What are the facts? Cambridge Carbon Footprint invites festival goers to â€˜What IS the deal with meat?â€™, a hot topic panel discussion and Q&A. <br/>Speakers, including leading figures on food sustainability Tara Garnett (founder of the Food Climate Research Network) and Clare Oxborrow (Head of the Land, Food and Water Team at FOE) will discuss the health, welfare and environmental issues related to the our ever increasing consumption of meat. Are there solutions out there? What technologies, policies and behaviour change might help? Join us in the beautiful setting of â€˜The Divinity Schoolâ€™ at St Johnâ€™s to find out more. <br/> <br/>Free event, no booking required.',	'2016-05-17 08:00:00',	'2016-05-17 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/what-is-the-deal-with-meat-cambridge-carbon-footprint-eat-festival/',	'All Saints Passage, St. John\'s Street, Cambridge, United Kingdom',	'2016-03-15 13:42:29',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/eat-cambridge-2016.png'),
(34342,	4,	'3835-1464170400-1464184800@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Healthy Eating Class @ Cambridge Cookery School',	'Cambridge Cookery school are now holding healthy eating cookery classes! Please see below for more details: <br/> <br/>\'â€œEat food. Not too much. Mostly plantsâ€ quote by Michael Pollan, one of our food heroes. We have created this class to share our passion for largely plant based food, seasonal and regional vegetables and with limited use of sustainable, welfare reared animal protein. We cover recipes involving most of the new super grains and cereals including quinoa, bulgur, black lentils, giant cous cous and Teff flour. We also show the huge versatility of humble vegetables such as celeriac, Jerusalem artichokes, beet root, courgette flowers â€“ all depending on what is in season. Our classes include welcome coffee and tea with cakes from our cafÃ©, full recipes packs, expert tuition and full back up for clearing away and assisting and we finish off with a communal lunch with wine.\'',	'2016-05-25 10:00:00',	'2016-05-25 14:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/healthy-eating-class-cambridge-cookery-school/',	'',	'2016-03-15 11:32:49',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/header_logo.jpg'),
