(41218,	4,	'3857-1462615200-1462640400@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Cambridge Sustainable Food at Eat Festival 2016',	'  <br/> <br/>Cambridge Sustainable food will again be at this yearâ€™s EAT Festival main event at the Corn Exchange on the 7th May, focusing on locally produced foods of all kinds. Weâ€™ll be running a lively interactive stall aiming to encourage people to buy, cook and eat food that is good for us and good for the planet, with questionnaires, quizzes, delicious tasters, recipes to give away. People can also find out where to buy sustainable food and which local food businesses have signed up to our new Sustainable Food Pledge. This is a really big, exciting event with lots of visitors! <br/> <br/>Volunteers are needed to help set up and run the stall for anything from 2 hours to all day if you wish. We need help from 10-5 on the day and it is a great chance for you to chat to the other stall holders too. <br/> <br/>If you would like to be involved in this great event, please email <a href=\"mailto:bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org\">bev@cambridgesustainablefood.org</a> or use our contact page.',	'2016-05-07 10:00:00',	'2016-05-07 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/cambridge-sustainable-food-at-eat-festival-2016/',	'Wheeler Street, Cambridge, CB2 3QB',	'2016-04-05 09:53:33',	'Eat%20Cambridge',	'hello@eat-cambridge.co.uk',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/eat.jpg'),
(41860,	4,	'3897-1462060800-1462233599@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Ely Food & Drink Festival 2016',	'Now in its third year, the Ely Food and Drink Festival, part of the Eel Festival weekend sees artisan traders, an expanded street food scene and celebrity chefs coming together outside the city\'s cathedral. Artisan, specialist food and drink traders will be housed in our main Food Hall with larger producers making up our Food and Drink Market. <br/> <br/>Further entertainment will be available throughout the city with our Bumper General Market being held in Market Place.  With many of the shops opening especially for the weekend, Ely will be buzzing!',	'2016-05-01 00:00:00',	'2016-05-02 00:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/ely-food-drink-festival-2016/',	'Ely Cathedral, Ely',	'2016-04-07 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/fanddfest151015.jpg'),
(41862,	4,	'3888-1462705200-1462710600@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Eat Cambridge Festival special â€“ introduction to Sour Dough',	'RETURNS FOR A 4TH YEAR! <br/> <br/>A one-off opportunity at a one-off price! <br/> <br/>This is a not-to-be-missed opportunity which sells out very fast! Cambridge Cookery School says \"A 90-minute mini master class by Artisan baker and founder of Cambridge Cookery School Tine Roche. Tine grew up with Scandinavian rye and sour dough and her teaching peels away much of the mystery surrounding the â€œking of breadsâ€. You will learn all there is to know about the amazing qualities of sour dough, you will bake a loaf to bring home and you will also leave with your own lively starter for years of successful sour dough baking to come.\" You can book here. <br/> <br/>This is a special class organised as part of the Eat Cambridge Festival.',	'2016-05-08 11:00:00',	'2016-05-08 12:30:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/eat-cambridge-festival-special-introduction-to-sour-dough/',	'',	'2016-04-07 09:56:01',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/breadmaking-crop-for-CM-140x160.jpg'),
(41863,	4,	'3901-1462993200-1463000400@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Raw Food Taster Evening',	'The Rocking Raw Chef rocks Hot Numbers with a threecourse raw food feast: sprouted crackers, flax tortillas, dips, warming soups, curries, veggie â€˜riceâ€™ and â€˜pastaâ€™, puddings, fruit crumbles, brownies and more. Everything is vegan, glutenfree, dairy-free. More than 10 different dishes, so come hungry. <br/> <br/>For more information see here. Book here.',	'2016-05-11 19:00:00',	'2016-05-11 21:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/raw-food-taster-evening/',	'Hot Numbers, Unit 6 Dales Brewery, Gwydir Street, Cambridge CB1 2LJ',	'2016-04-07 16:20:22',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Veggie_Latkes2_Hollandaise-780x519.jpg'),
(41864,	4,	'3900-1463324400-1463331600@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'The Eat Cambridge Food Debate',	' <br/> <br/>The Eat Cambridge festival of local food and drink presents... the Eat Cambridge Food Debate <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>Cambridge Food: Art or Science? Back by popular demand, this yearâ€™s Eat Cambridge Food Debate explores the relationship between art and science where our local food scene is concerned. Chaired by food and consumer scientist Dr Sue Bailey, the panel of local experts, chefs, and foodies will question where food creativity, hobbies, and experiences, meet the worlds of science, technology, and industrial production. Panel to be announced! <br/> <br/>This event is part of the Eat Cambridge festival, an annual food and drink festival showcasing Cambridgeshireâ€™s independent food scene. Founded in 2013 and taking place for two weeks every May, the festival features the best, newest, and most exciting independent food and drink in the area. Find out more: www.eat-cambridge.co.uk.  <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>',	'2016-05-15 15:00:00',	'2016-05-15 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/the-eat-cambridge-food-debate/',	'',	'2016-04-07 15:47:56',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/2015-Eat-Cambridge-Logo-NEW.png'),
(41867,	4,	'3894-1464714000-1464721200@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Ethical Consumerism: Good for the Food System? Hosted by CRASSH',	'Speakers:  Sushil Mohan (Business School, Brighton) <br/>Fair trade without the froth <br/>Bev Sedley (Cambridge Sustainable Food) <br/>The Cambridge Sustainable Food Charter <br/> <br/>Consumers shape the food system by the products they choose to purchase. Increasingly, consumers in more economically developed countries are choosing locally sourced, organic and fair trade products. This seminar will explore the rationale for and the consequences of these choices. Does fair trade in fact produce positive outcomes for the food system? Do organic foods have any nutritional benefits over conventional foods? We will also explore what is being done locally in Cambridge to promote a sustainable food system. <br/> <br/>Open to all.  Registration for sessions is encouraged, please email to Luke (<a href=\"mailto:lab70@cam.ac.uk\">lab70@cam.ac.uk</a>) or Greg (<a href=\"mailto:gjm38@cam.ac.uk\">gjm38@cam.ac.uk</a>) <br/>Part of the Food: Field to Table? Research Group, series <br/> <br/>Administrative assistance: <a href=\"mailto:gradfac@crassh.cam.ac.uk\">gradfac@crassh.cam.ac.uk</a> <br/> <br/> ',	'2016-05-31 17:00:00',	'2016-05-31 19:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/ethical-consumerism-good-for-the-food-system-hosted-by-crassh/',	'7 West Road, Cambridge, Cambridge',	'2016-04-07 14:36:06',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Food_field_to_table_evf.jpg'),
(41868,	6,	'13010-1460482200-1460491200@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Centre for Global Equality AGM 2016',	' <br/>Annual General Meeting 2016 <br/>  <br/> <br/>Join the Centre for Global Equality and our trustees, partners and supporters at the Annual General Meeting 2016. <br/> <br/>To be held on Tuesday the 12th of April 2016 at 5.30pm at the Yusuf Hamied Theatre, Christs College, Cambridge, CB2 3BU <br/> <br/>We will be providing a financial review, as well as appointing possible new members to the Board of Trustees. <br/> <br/>Once the formal AGM has finished, we will be holding a participatory workshop to establish the Centre for Global Equality\'s Special Interest Groups (SIGs). These are small groups of people within our network, who are passionate about a particular topic that they would like to work together on with fellow members and supporters of CGE. They can be defined by sector, country or challenge; this initiative will encourage like-minded members to meet and contribute to projects they have a particular interest in. <br/> <br/>Please see below for further information and click here to confirm your attendance. <br/>Click here for information from previous AGMs.',	'2016-04-12 17:30:00',	'2016-04-12 20:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/centre-global-equality-agm-2016/',	'Christs College, Cambridge, CB2 3BU, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-07 17:55:12',	'',	'',	''),
