(42195,	6,	'13057-1460482200-1460491200@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Annual General Meeting',	' <br/> <br/>The Annual General Meeting provides an opportunity for members and supporters interested in the Centre for Global Equalityâ€™s work to reconnect with each other, share experiences, reflect on an eventful year and look ahead towards exciting future developments. <br/> <br/>We will be providing a financial review, as well as appointing possible new members to the Board of Trustees. Subsequently, we will provide any proposed resolutions before finalising with any other business. <br/> <br/>Once the formal AGM has finished, we will be holding a participatory workshop to establish the Centre for Global Equalityâ€™s Special Interest Groups (SIGs). These are small groups of people within our network, who are passionate about a particular topic that they would like to work together on with fellow members and supporters of CGE. They can be defined by sector, country or challenge; this initiative will encourage like-minded members to meet and contribute to projects they have a particular interest in. <br/> <br/>Click here to confirm your attendance. <br/> <br/>Click here for information from previous AGMs. <br/> <br/>See below for links to supporting documents; <br/> <br/>2015-08-12_AGM-Minutes-2015  <br/> <br/>2016-03-24_CGE AGM Agenda  <br/> <br/>2016-03-24_Proposed new trustee details  <br/> <br/>Annual Report & Financial Statements 2014-2015  <br/> <br/>HC Trustee Rotation Proposal 2015 AGM',	'2016-04-12 17:30:00',	'2016-04-12 20:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/annual-general-meeting/',	'Christs College, Cambridge, CB2 3BU, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-08 08:55:46',	'',	'',	''),
