(43514,	4,	'3942-1466640000-1466812799@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Cambridge Conference on Global Food Security 2016',	'The Cambridge Global Food Security Initiative, the Cambridge Conservation Initiative and the Cambridge Centre for Development Studies has collaborated to bring a conference looking at the interaction of food security with conservation, economics, culture and politics. <br/> <br/>The conference is spread across two days. Thursday afternoon (23 June) will be given to scene-setting on the challenges of our changing world and the current course of research activity that seeks to meet them. Friday (24 June) will be devoted to more focused presentation and discussion of key areas. <br/> <br/>    Current research activities. <br/>    Food security, sustainability and conservation. <br/>    Economics, culture and politics of food. <br/> <br/>More information and registration is available here <br/> <br/>Bookings are now open. Tickets are available at £39 (standard) and £19.50 (students) for the Thursday and Friday programmes, with reduced prices for attending either one of the days. Refreshments including a buffet lunch on the Friday are included.',	'2016-06-23 00:00:00',	'2016-06-24 00:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/cambridge-conference-global-food-security-2016/',	'The David Attenborough Building, New Museums Site, Pembroke Street, Cambridge, CB2 3QZ',	'2016-04-12 00:00:00',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/5445528297_6f30d63cc8_z.jpg'),
