(44498,	4,	'3965-1461348000-1461351600@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Talk: \"Feeding the world without costing the earth\"',	'Meeting food demand at least cost to wild species and the benefits they provide us is one of this centuryâ€™s greatest challenges. Is it better to adopt wildlife-friendly on-farm practices (land sharing), or to maximise farm yields and spare other land for conservation (land sparing), or something in between? In this talk, Andrew Balmford will describe a model for evaluating these and intermediate strategies, parameterise this for five parts of the world and several different taxa, extend the analysis to consider the impact of land sparing on greenhouse gas emissions, and begin to explore policy mechanisms for those land-use strategies which hold most promise for nature.',	'2016-04-22 18:00:00',	'2016-04-22 19:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/ccf-summer-symposium-2016-food-security-sustainability-conservation/',	'Clare College, Cambridge, CB3 9AJ, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-15 16:36:39',	'',	'',	''),
