(46176,	21,	'e1708050892792974@facebook.com',	'TONIGHT: Why the climate crisis can help us reclaim democracy (panel discussion).',	'Climate change is often presentedto us as an abstract scientific issue and yet its consequences haveprofound implications on every aspect of our lives. To tackle the climate crisis does not only mean more people turning off their lights and recycling - it requires thatwe re-think the way our society runs; in its political systems, in business practices etc.  <br/> <br/>Climate justice movements across the worldare growing in their demands for a fossil free future, and for a fair and justice transition.  <br/> <br/>But in changing the way our system runs, can the climate crisis actually help us reclaim our democracy?  <br/> <br/>Join Zero Carbon and guest speakers:  <br/> <br/>SUZANNE JEFFERY (Chair of the Campaign Against Climate Change and the CCC Trade Union Group) <br/> <br/>OSCAR GILLESPIE (Green Party Councillor in Cambridge, worked with FossilFree Cambridgeshire) <br/> <br/>ANGUS SATOW(Co-founder of the Cambridge University divestment campaign and campaigns officer at Zero Carbon) <br/> <br/>Hope to see you there, in the run upto our March for Divestment (April 30th).  <a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/1672315446364128/\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.facebook.com/events/1672315446364128/</a>  <br/> <br/>All welcome! <br/> <br/><a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/1672315446364128/\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.facebook.com/events/1672315446364128/</a> ',	'2016-04-26 18:30:00',	'2016-04-26 21:30:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/1708050892792974/',	'Keynes Hall, King\'s College',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Cambridge Zero Carbon Society',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
(46177,	21,	'e255843954749967@facebook.com',	'How responsible finance can transform markets - Georg Kell at Cambridge',	'\'A silent revolution: How responsible finance can transform markets\' <br/> <br/>Join us for an inspiring talk by Georg Kell, founder and former Executive Director of UN Global Compact, on corporate responsibility and using responsible finance to transform markets.  <br/> <br/>The event is hosted by Positive Investment Cambridge, a coalition that works to ensure that the University and its colleges engage in socially and environmentally responsible investment practices. <br/> <br/>Register for your *free* ticket on Eventbrite: www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/how-responsible-finance-can-change-the-world-georg-kell-in-cambridge-tickets-24364853934 <br/> <br/>Background links:  <br/>- Georg Kell on corporate responsibility: <a href=\'http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122</a>   <br/>- Positive Investment Cambridge: <a href=\'http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122</a>  <br/> <br/><a href=\'http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.un.org/apps/news/newsmakers.asp?NewsID=122</a> ',	'2016-04-26 18:00:00',	'2016-04-26 19:30:00',	'http://www.facebook.com/events/255843954749967/',	'Old Divinity School, St John\'s College',	'0000-00-00 00:00:00',	'Positive Investment Cambridge',	'noreply@facebookmail.com',	''),
