(48490,	4,	'4016-1462617000-1462624200@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Weaning Matters Workshop: Growing a Healthy Eater',	'This 2-hour workshop will cover 4 topics which often concern families wanting to know how best to wean their children and develop healthy eating habits: <br/>  <br/>Growth and Development <br/>Introduction and overview <br/>Dr Camilla Salvestrini, Consultant Paediatric Gastroeneterologist <br/>  <br/>Foods and Nutrition <br/>What, when and how much? <br/>Carine Henry, Registered Dietician, Paediatric Specialist <br/> <br/>Skills and Communication <br/>â€œI know what I can do; I know what I likeâ€ <br/>Cathy Davies, Speech and Language Therapist <br/>  <br/>Weaning and the Family <br/>Taking the worry out of weaning <br/>Dr Caroline Lindsay, Clinical Psychologist <br/> <br/>The price of £60 per family will include refreshments. To book please email <a href=\"mailto:weaning@paediatricnutrition.com\">weaning@paediatricnutrition.com</a>.',	'2016-05-07 10:30:00',	'2016-05-07 12:30:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/weaning-matters-workshop-growing-healthy-eater/',	'Cipher House, Trumpington, CB2 9LG, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-27 12:49:01',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_1349-1.jpeg'),
(48491,	4,	'4012-1462703400-1462726800@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Transition Cambridge Event: All about healthy soil talk/workshop + community garden day',	'Like to grow your own fruit and veg? Involved in a community garden or orchard? Join Transition Cambridge at Empty Common Community Garden for a workshop on healthy soil - the basis of all that grows. What is healthy soil? How can you improve the soil on your patch - and benefit from better crops? Come to the garden any time from 10.30 to join the regular gardening activities, or from 1pm (approx) for a picnic lunch (bring food to share or a picnic for yourself). The soil workshop (from 2-3pm) will be led by Charlotte Synge, the garden coordinator and permaculturist. There will be plenty of time for questions. If you want to bring a sample of the soil from your own garden to take a look at, please do. The garden is off Brooklands Avenue, near the Trumpington Road traffic lights. There is a black gate, and the garden is at the south end of the allotments. More info on the garden here or take at look at the event on the Transition Cambridge website. Come and share the beauty and community spirit of this special community space!',	'2016-05-08 10:30:00',	'2016-05-08 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/transition-cambridge-event-healthy-soil-talkworkshop-community-garden-day/',	'',	'2016-04-27 12:12:13',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/transition-cambridge-community-garden.jpg'),
