(48824,	6,	'13090-1462456800-1462471200@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Innovations in Agri-Tech',	' <br/> <br/>Join us for a seminar on Agri-Tech, innovative agricultural technical developments to increase sustainable crop production, through data-driven precision agriculture and genetic plant protection techniques, with emphasis on cropping in East Africa and the ultimate relevance of the techniques to small farmers. Dr Stephanie Race, CropPerformance Ltd, will talk on â€˜Sustainable Perennial Crop Production in the Tropics:   understanding yield variation under a changing climateâ€™. Professor Sir David Baulcombe, Department of Plant Sciences, Cambridge, will talk on â€˜Biotechnology to control disease in African cropsâ€™. <br/> <br/>The seminar is being organised by the Tropical Agriculture Association (TAA) East Anglia Branch, the Centre for Global Equality (CGE), CambPlants Hub and the University of Cambridge Strategic Research Initiative in Global Food Security (GFSI). <br/> <br/>For more information and to book your place, click here. <br/> <br/> ',	'2016-05-05 14:00:00',	'2016-05-05 18:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/innovations-agri-tech/',	'Cambridge University, Bateman Street, Cambridge, CB2 1LR, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-29 09:45:15',	'',	'',	''),
(48826,	6,	'13096-1462993200-1463000400@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Celebrating Fairtrade in Cambridge',	'Come and discuss the significance of Fairtrade in the city of Cambridge. This event will bring together organisations associated with Fairtrade and raise awareness of FT activity amongst shops, cafÃ©s, schools, places of worship, campaigning organisations and others. Barbara Crowther from the Fairtrade foundation will give the keynote address at the meeting. <br/> <br/>Refreshments will be sponsored by suppliers of Fairtrade products. There will also be stalls with Fairtrade products. <br/> <br/>For further details and to register, please click here.',	'2016-05-11 19:00:00',	'2016-05-11 21:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/13096/',	'',	'2016-04-29 10:05:36',	'',	'',	''),
(48827,	6,	'13101-1463400000-1463405400@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Entrepreneurship in Silicon Fen: Trends and Opportunities',	'Join us for the next T4D Hub Lunch & Learn, as we take a tour of the history of entrepreneurship in \"Silicon Fen\" and the trends in this rapidly evolving ecosystem that may helpâ€”or hinderâ€”our own aspirations. Our speaker will be Stew McTavish, Head of IdeaSpace and an expert on the Cambridge entrepreneurship scene. Stew has spent much of the past decade working in, around, and for the Cambridge entrepreneurial community. He\'s seen what has been funded, what has grown, and what has exploded spectacularly and will be able to provide an inside look to participants at this lunchtime talk. <br/> <br/>To book your place, click here to email Julia at Simprints. Please book at least 24 hours in advance.',	'2016-05-16 12:00:00',	'2016-05-16 13:30:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/entrepreneurship-silicon-fen-trends-opportunities/',	'Chapel Street, Cambridge, United Kingdom',	'2016-04-29 10:05:09',	'',	'',	''),
