(56935,	6,	'13189-1466841600-1466877600@centreforglobalequality.org',	'Technology Ventures Conference (TVC): The Circular Economy',	'CUTEC is the leading student-run technology and entrepreneurship society at Cambridge University. Founded in 2003, CUTEC now boasts 4,000+ members worldwide. <br/> <br/>Join them for the 13th annual Technology Ventures Conference with over 300 investors, researchers, entrepreneurs, and policy-makers to innovate our way to a cleaner, healthier, more efficient future. By re-imagining waste as a resource, we will advance science, develop new technologies, and create novel market opportunities. We will dive into the fields of biotech, medicine, materials, AI, fintech, consumer goods - all through the lens of waste as a resource. <br/> <br/>Where: St. Paul\'s Church, Hills Road, Cambridge, CB2 1JP <br/>When: Saturday June 25th, 8am to 6pm <br/> <br/>To find out more and purchase tickets, please visit the website.',	'2016-06-25 08:00:00',	'2016-06-25 18:00:00',	'http://centreforglobalequality.org/event/technology-ventures-conference-tvc-circular-economy/',	'Hills Road, Cambridge, CB2 1JP, United Kingdom',	'2016-05-18 14:34:32',	'',	'',	''),
