(82677,	4,	'4717-1473328800-1473354000@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Rescue cabbages, broccoli, marrows with Gleaning Network!',	'We\'ve had a message from The East of England Gleaning Network that they need as many volunteers as possible to rescue thousands of cabbages, broccoli and marrows going to waste on a farm near King\'s Lynn. If you are interested in helping, read their email below - you can sign up here. Some financial help with transport (see below). <br/> <br/>\"Hello great and good gleaners of East of England! <br/> <br/>Gleaning day coming up Thursday 8th Septemberâ€“ 10am-5pm (TBC): <br/>We\'ve discovered thousands of cabbage, broccoli and marrows going to waste on a farm near Kings Lynn- equal to 1000\'s of PORTIONS! <br/> <br/>Theyâ€™re being wasted because they are outgrades, trial crops and some just couldnâ€™t be sold. <br/> <br/>But these cabbage, marrows and broccoli are perfectly delicious and nutritious, so we\'re setting out to save as many as possible for charity, and we NEED YOUR HELP. The more volunteers we have, the more we can save! <br/> <br/>Next Thursday 8th September 10am-5pm (TBC) weâ€™re inviting volunteers to the farm to help harvest that tasty cabbage, marrows and broccoli and save them from waste, to supply food poverty charities like FareShare with beautiful food. Witness the colossal waste first-hand, and have a great social day out for a fantastic cause. Check out these photo highlights on Facebook from our gleans over the years. <br/> <br/>Unfortunately, this gleaning day is not suitable for children under the age of 18, as it involves use of harvesting knives, but we have another glean coming in the next few weeks that will be. <br/> <br/>So please spread the news to your friends and groups, by sharing this email. <br/>*** <br/>To join the gleaning day, please fill in our sign-up sheet <br/>or for more info, please contact eastengland@feedbackglobal.org <br/>*** <br/> <br/>Please get in touch ASAP so we have an idea of numbers. Also, please do check whether you can make it, as lots of drop-outs at the last minute can jeopardize the gleaning day going ahead. <br/> <br/>Travel expenses can be covered for those travelling from Cambridgeshire, Norfolk and South Lincs â€“ just check with us first (we cover up to £12 per gleaner). <br/> <br/>Here\'s some background about gleaning: <br/>Gleaning Network is on a mission to save the estimated 3 million tonnes of food that are wasted on farms every year in the UK â€“ we salvage healthy, edible fruit and vegetables that farmers cannot sell, and get it to those who need it, like homeless hostels and food poverty charities. Volunteers harvest the food in fun days out on farms, making a difference to their community and connecting with their food. We raise awareness of the causes of food waste, and campaign to design food waste out of the system, for the good of people and the planet. <br/> <br/>From our start in 2012 to the end of 2015, the Gleaning Network already gleaned over 188 tonnes of produce, equal to well over 2 million portions of fruit and veg, with over 1000 volunteers across 99 gleaning days. Read more about the Gleaning Network! <br/> <br/>Jannine Parry <br/>East England Gleaning Coordinator',	'2016-09-08 10:00:00',	'2016-09-08 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/rescue-cabbages-broccoli-marrows-gleaning-network/',	'',	'2016-09-01 15:40:06',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Gelaning-cauliflowers1.jpg'),
