(88131,	4,	'4616-1474799400-1474822800@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Milton Park Autumn Festival',	'Milton Country Park\'s annual Autumn Festival is a great family day out. There will be stalls with delicous local produce including ales and cider, live music, and activities the whole family will enjoy such as hover craft rides on the lake! Cambridge Sustainable Food will have a stall with information, food samples and family friendly activities. The event is free for under 16s. See here for more information and tickets.',	'2016-09-25 10:30:00',	'2016-09-25 17:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/autumn-festival/',	'Milton, Cambridge, CB24 6AZ',	'2016-08-15 11:11:46',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/autumn-fest-pic.jpg'),
(88132,	4,	'4213-1475143500-1475157600@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Cambridge Cookery School Healthy Eating Class',	'This class focuses on healthy eating using seasonal, local and largely plant-based ingredients, please note that it is not exclusively vegetarian. The cost includes recipe packs, coffee and a communal lunch - please see website for further details.<a href=\'http://www.cambridgecookeryschool.com/classes/instructive-cookery-classes/2016/09/healthy-eating-.\' target=\'_blank\'>http://www.cambridgecookeryschool.com/classes/instructive-cookery-classes/2016/09/healthy-eating-.</a>  <br/> <br/>  <br/> <br/> ',	'2016-09-29 10:05:00',	'2016-09-29 14:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/cambridge-cookery-school-healthy-eating-class/',	'',	'2016-06-20 13:05:54',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/image-161x210.jpg'),
(88133,	4,	'4458-1475316000-1475330400@www.cambridgesustainablefood.org',	'Histon and Impington Village Food Festival',	'~ a Food Festival for all the Family ~ <br/> <br/>Organised by Histon & Impington Sustainability Group (HISG) and Histon & Impington Community Orchard Project (HICOP), this festival is a real Autumn delight. Taking place in the Community Orchard itself, this foody festival has plenty of activities for young and old, as well as opportunities to learn about, give and buy food. <br/> <br/>Activities will include: <br/> <br/>     Pulp friction: Make your own smoothies with pedal power <br/>     Quizzes and juicing activities for children <br/>     Try your hand at juicing - bring your fruit, take juice home meet the experts <br/>     Local beekeeper with honey for sale <br/>     Wildlife Trust advising on food plants for garden wildlife <br/>     Allotment growing advice <br/>     Food for Free expert - advice on safe foraging in the countryside <br/>     Bring your apples to be identified <br/>     Local poultry breeder providing advice and hens for sale <br/>     Fruit and vegetable growing advice, composting tips and food plants for sale <br/>     Expert on growing food in small spaces <br/>     Local food vendors, tea and cake stall, smoothies <br/>     Surplus stall- swap or donate your excess fruit and vegetables <br/>     Find out what HI Sustainability Group are doing <br/> <br/> ',	'2016-10-01 10:00:00',	'2016-10-01 14:00:00',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/event/histon-impington-village-food-festival/',	'Somerset Road, Histon, CB24 9JS',	'2016-09-13 12:50:32',	'',	'',	'http://www.cambridgesustainablefood.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/HIVFF_logo_trans.png'),
